<TITLE> Schools to clear schedules by Dec 4 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 19 (bdnews24.com)The education ministry has also asked all educational institutions in the capital and elsewhere in the country to wind up their current year's activities, including all examinations, by Dec 4 in preparation for the Jatiya Sangsad election scheduled for Dec 18. The ministry will be sending out circulars to this effect to all concerned in a day or two, education adviser Hossain Zillur Rahman told reporters Sunday. Speaking after and education ministry meet, Hossain Zillur also said education officials have been asked to ensure that schools strictly adhere to new morning schedules to ease traffic gridlock in the city, he said. At a meeting on city school timings to ward off traffic gridlock, the adviser told those present, including the education secretary and the education directorate chief, to enforce the new timings. City schools have been asked to start their morning classes between 7:30-8:30 am. "Eighteen teams headed by 36 deputy secretaries will roam the metropolitan zones to ensure that all schools adhere to the time slot indicated by the ministry directive," said the adviser. bdnews24.
